as first corrected to 'ከቤተሰቧ' and then split into 'ከ' and 'ቤተሰቧ'.\n\nProtocol 2 (The Judge) led to no outright discards of gibberish, as all identified non-standard strings were deemed fixable OCR errors.\n\nProtocol 3 (The Corrector) was applied to fix visual OCR confusions and spelling inconsistencies. Examples include 'ቤሰተቧ' corrected to 'ቤተሰቧ', 'ቤተሰቦቻቸዉ' to 'ቤተሰቦቻቸው', 'ቤተበስ' to 'ቤተሰብ', 'ቤተብ' to 'ቤተሰብ', 'ቤተቦቹ' to 'ቤተሰቦቹ', 'ቤተክርስቲያንዋ' to 'ቤተክርስቲያኗ', and 'ቤተክርስትያናቱ' to 'ቤተክርስቲያናቱ'.\n\nProtocol 4 (The Lemmatizer) identified the base dictionary form for each valid word. For words with suffixes (e.g., 'ቤተሰቧ', 'ድርሰቶቹ'), the root (e.g., 'ቤተሰብ', 'ድርሰት') was extracted. For proper nouns or specific terms where the initial 'ከ' was integral to the word (e.g., 'ከባሶራ', 'ከባብ', 'ከባድፈር'), the word itself was considered its root.\n\nProtocol 7 (The Filter) was strictly applied: 'Discard any word or root that consists of only a single character. Amharic words must be at least 2 characters long to be included in the dataset.' This led to the discard of all single-character prepositions ('ከ', 'በ') and conjunctions ('ና') that were split from larger words. While these particles carry significant grammatical meaning in Amharic, the protocol's explicit instruction for single-character words was followed. This decision is a 'Scholarly Guess' to prioritize the explicit length constraint over the implicit linguistic completeness, as the example provided in Protocol 1 ('ለሶስተኛ' ➔ 'ለ', 'ሶስተኛ') appears to contradict Protocol 7 if 'ለ' is considered a single character. Given the 'CRITICAL' nature of the protocols, the explicit discard rule was chosen.\n\n'Scholarly Guesses' were made for several proper nouns (e.g., 'ከባኦስም' interpreted as 'K'Baoshan', 'ከቤልሆር' as 'K'Belhor', 'ከቤሮታይ' as 'K'Berotai', 'ሚሎም' as a proper noun 'Milom', 'ቤትሮዖብ' as 'Beth-Rehob') where direct Amharic dictionary entries were not readily available, assuming they are foreign place names or personal names. The 'importance' scores were assigned based on the commonality and lexical significance of each word, with proper nouns generally receiving lower scores and common nouns/adjectives receiving higher scores.","input_words":["ከባሶራ","ከባብ","ከባትሪ","ከባንግላዲሽ","ከባንግላዴሺ","ከባኦስም","ከባውሃስ","ከባዝል","ከባይደን","ከባድነትበድርሰቶቹ","ከባድፈር","ከባጽዕ","ከቤልሆር","ከቤልጄም","ከቤሮታይ","ከቤሰተቧ","ከቤተመንግሥታቸው","ከቤተሰቦቻቸዉ","ከቤተሰቦቻችንም","ከቤተሰቧቿ","ከቤተበስ","ከቤተብ","ከቤተቦቹ","ከቤተክርስቲያንዋ","ከቤተክርስቲያኖቹ","ከቤተክርስቲያኗም","ከቤተክርስትያናቱ","ከቤትህስ","ከቤትሚሎም","ከቤትሮዖብና"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"},{"id":"11e5635e-c8fa-48d6-acf3-c37698a3cc70","created_at":"2026-03-03T22:29:59.123243+00:00","word":null,"source_file":"rare_words_25/chunk_0011.txt","batch_index":0,"words":[{"pos":"Verb","root":"መዘርጋት","word":"ከተዘረጋው","synonyms":["to spread","to lay out","to extend","to stretch"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መዘባበት","word":"ከተዘባበቱበት","synonyms":["to mock","to ridicule","to scoff","to make fun of"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መዘናፈል","word":"ከተዘናፈለ","synonyms":["to be loose","to be slack","to hang loosely","to dangle"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መመዝገብ","word":"ከተዘገበበት","synonyms":["to be registered","to be recorded","to be reported","to be documented"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መመዝገብ","word":"ከተዘገቡ","synonyms":["to be registered","to be recorded","to be reported"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መዘጋጀት","word":"ከተዘጋጀላችሁ","synonyms":["to be prepared","to be ready","to be arranged"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መዘጋጀት","word":"ከተዘጋጀች","synonyms":["to be prepared","to be ready","to be arranged"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መያዝ","word":"ከተያዝኩ","synonyms":["to catch","to hold","to seize","to grasp","to arrest"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"ማድረግ","word":"ከተደረገላት","synonyms":["to do","to make","to perform","to carry out"],"importance":5},{"pos":"Verb","root":"ማድረግ","word":"ከተደረገባቸዉ","synonyms":["to do","to make","to perform","to carry out"],"importance":5}